focus on Emerald Lake in Sequoia National Park, the book marshals long-term limnological and ecological data to provide a detailed and synthetic account of these processes, while also highlighting the vulnerability of Sierra lakes to changes in climate and atmospheric deposition. In so doing, it lays the scientific foundations for predicting and understanding how the lake will respond.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aLakesxEnvironmental aspectszSierra Nevada (Calif. and Nev.) 0aLakesxEnvironmental aspectszSierra Nevada (Calif. and Nev.). 0aWatershedsxEnvironmental aspectszSierra Nevada (Calif. and Nev.) 0aWatershedsxEnvironmental aspectszSierra Nevada (Calif. and Nev.). 7aNATURE / Ecology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070480808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2020z9783110704600oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520967342zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520967342423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520967342.jpg  a978-3-11-069041-5  UC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070480-8  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DPMb2020